==Latin==
===Etymology===
Proto-Indo-European [[*gerə-]] ("to cry hoarsely"). [[Cognate]] to English [[crane]], but not to [[grouse]], which has an unknown etymology.

===Noun===
'''grus''' {{f}} (''plural:'' '''grues''')

# [[crane]], a bird also eaten as food
# a type of [[siege]] weapon

